                        <span class="glyphicon glyphicon-circle-arrow-right" aria-hidden="true"/></a></p><p class="indent"><span class="tei-listPerson">
                    <span class="tei-person">
                        <span class="tei-persName"> Paul </span>
                    </span>
                </span> <a href="/8559-423" class="factoid-more">See factoid page
                        <span class="glyphicon glyphicon-circle-arrow-right" aria-hidden="true"/></a></p><h4>Death: </h4><p class="indent"><span class="spearLabel">Death date: </span>30 October A. D.
                                        52630 Teshri I A. Gr.
                                        838 <a href="/8559-492" class="factoid-more"> See factoid page <span class="glyphicon glyphicon-circle-arrow-right" aria-hidden="true"/></a></p><h4>Sex: </h4><p class="indent"><span class="tei-persName"> Paul
                                </span> was male. <a href="/8559-424" class="factoid-more">See factoid page
                        <span class="glyphicon glyphicon-circle-arrow-right" aria-hidden="true"/></a></p><h4>Occupation(s): </h4><p class="indent"><span class="tei-persName">Pawlā</span> was Bishop of <span class="tei-placeName"> Edessa </span>. <a href="/8559-425" class="factoid-more">See factoid page
                        <span class="glyphicon glyphicon-circle-arrow-right" aria-hidden="true"/></a></p></div><div class="sources"><h3>Relationships</h3><p class="indent">Patricius, Justin I and Pawla had a professional relationship. <a href="/8559-463" class="factoid-more">See factoid page
                        <span class="glyphicon glyphicon-circle-arrow-right" aria-hidden="true"/></a></p><p class="indent">Justinian I, Euphrasios and Pawla had a professional relationship. <a href="/8559-489" class="factoid-more">See factoid page
                        <span class="glyphicon glyphicon-circle-arrow-right" aria-hidden="true"/></a></p></div><div class="sources"><h3>Events</h3><p class="indent"> After 
                                10 April A. D.
                                        510
                                the Sabbath of the
                                        Resurrection A. Gr. 821
                             Pawlā
                             became Bishop of  Edessa .  <a href="/8559-428" class="factoid-more">See factoid page
                        <span class="glyphicon glyphicon-circle-arrow-right" aria-hidden="true"/></a></p><hr/><p class="indent"> On 
                                4 November A. D.
                                        519
                                4 Teshri II A. Gr.
                                        831
                             Patricius
                             arrived in 
                                Edessa  at the command of  the Emperor Justin 
                            in order to urge  Bishop
                                Pawlā  to receive the Council of  Chalcedon  or else
                            be deposed.  <a href="/8559-464" class="factoid-more">See factoid page
                        <span class="glyphicon glyphicon-circle-arrow-right" aria-hidden="true"/></a></p><hr/><p class="indent"> After 
                                4 November A. D.
                                        519
                                4 Teshri II A. Gr.
                                        831
                            ,  Bishop Pawlā
                             refused to accept the Council of  Chalcedon  . When
                                 Patricius
                             threatened to remove him from  Edessa  he fled to
                            the  House of Baptism
                            . Fearing the command of  Emperor Justin ,
                                 Patricius
                             removed 
                                Bishop Pawlā  to  Seleucia .  <a href="/8559-465" class="factoid-more">See factoid page
                        <span class="glyphicon glyphicon-circle-arrow-right" aria-hidden="true"/></a></p><hr/><p class="indent"> In 
                                520/1
                                A. Gr.
                                        832
                            , the  Emperor
                                Justin  returned  Bishop Pawlā  to
                            his episcopal see in 
                                Edessa  hoping that he would accept the Council of
                                 Chalcedon
                             .  <a href="/8559-466" class="factoid-more">See factoid page
                        <span class="glyphicon glyphicon-circle-arrow-right" aria-hidden="true"/></a></p><hr/><p class="indent"> Pawlā 
                            refused to accept the Council of  Chalcedon  and on 
                                27 July 27 A. D.
                                        522
                                27 Tammuz A. Gr.
                                        833
                             Emperor Justin
                             deposed him and exiled him to  Euchata .  <a href="/8559-467" class="factoid-more">See factoid page
                        <span class="glyphicon glyphicon-circle-arrow-right" aria-hidden="true"/></a></p><hr/><p class="indent"> After 
                                27 June 525
                                27 Ḥazirān A. Gr.
                                        836
                            ,  Pawlā
                             repented of his opposition to the Council of  Chalcedon  ,
                            petitioned  Justinian
                             for the return of his episcopal see, and wrote a libellus
                            affirming the council to 
                                Euphrasius the Patriarch .  <a href="/8559-490" class="factoid-more">See factoid page
                        <span class="glyphicon glyphicon-circle-arrow-right" aria-hidden="true"/></a></p><hr/><p class="indent"> Following  Pawlā's
                             acceptance of the Council of  Chalcedon  and a
                            letter of support from 
                                Justinian ,  the Emperor Justin 
                            restored  Pawlā
                             to his episcopal see and he entered  Edessa  on 
                                8 March 526
                                8 Ādar A. Gr.
                                        837
                            .  <a href="/8559-491" class="factoid-more">See factoid page
                        <span class="glyphicon glyphicon-circle-arrow-right" aria-hidden="true"/></a></p><hr/><p class="indent"> On 
                                30 October A. D.
                                        526
                                30 Teshri I A. Gr.
                                        838
                             Pawlā
                             died.  <a href="/8559-493" class="factoid-more">See factoid page
                        <span class="glyphicon glyphicon-circle-arrow-right" aria-hidden="true"/></a></p><hr/></div><div class="citation"><h3>How to cite:</h3><span class="element">
